The paper proposes a convolutional neural network based encoder-decoder architecture for image steganography, which involves hiding images as payload in cover images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new loss function and performs extensive empirical evaluation, which could potentially fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories.
